<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
The call computes (NULL == key) ? 0 : strlen(key) and passes that length to MHD_lookup_connection_value_n which, when key is non-NULL, will call MHD_str_equal_caseless_bin_n_(key, pos->header, key_size). If that binary n-byte comparison routine uses memcmp (very likely, given the name), this results in memcmp being used to compare null-terminated strings (length derived from strlen), which violates MISRA C 2023 Rule 21.14. In other words, passing strlen(key) into a binary comparison routine can lead to memcmp being used to compare null-terminated strings.
</scenario>
